items.name: Akhtar Samosa
items.description: As the name suggests, this shop is popular for it's samosas
items.brandLongDescription: Rumour has it that Akhtar Bhai was the first one to sell samosas in Pune. We don’t know what the truth is, a bite of the delicious Mutton Samosa here and you won’t care either. The thin pastry (patti) casing is crisp, not too oily or greasy and generously stuffed. Highly recommended are the chicken and mutton samosa, both of which have spicy keema filling.

items.name: Arthurs Theme
items.brandLongDescription: Unveiling the mysteries of European dishes, Arthur's Theme in Pune is one of its kind restaurant in Pune. The extensive menu at Arthur's Theme in Pune has interesting options to choose from. Apart from the regular starters and main course, they serve Don Quixote, Queen Marchell, Alfredo, Honey & Mustard Salad, Hawaiian Salad, Roberto, Hazen, Colombus, Venetia Pasta, Nicole Pasta, Lady Jennifer Prawns, Charles the Bond, Mazini, Madoch and a variety of Fish items.

items.name: Atithi
items.brandLongDescription: A casual dining restaurant located in Pune. This Restaurant strive to provide you delicious food with excellent quality. It offers a menu of different cuisine.

items.name: Bedekar Misal Pav
items.brandLongDescription: Tucked away in an obscure lane near Patrya Maruti Mandir in Narayan Peth, Bedekar MIsal Pav is one of the most popular misal pav joints in Pune. It has been in operation for over 70 years, when it was founded in 1948 by Dattaray Bedekar

items.name: Blue Nile Restaurant
items.brandLongDescription: Established in the early 1960s, the restaurant was initially named Nanking Cafe. Over five decades, Blue Nile rose to the fame it boasts of now! With its retro Indian ambience, wooden furniture and spacious dining halls, eating hereÂ is close to a tradition that has been going strong through generations.

items.name: Burger-Since 1989
items.brandLongDescription: Burger-Since 1989

items.name: Cafe Goodluck
items.brandLongDescription: One of the best-known Irani Cafés we explored in Pune is Café Good Luck, replete with a namesake chowk – Good Luck Chowk.

items.name: Cake N Counter
items.brandLongDescription: One of the good bakeries in Pune, known for it's fancy cakes

items.name: Chinar
items.brandLongDescription: One of the most popular Kashmiri restaurant in Pune, it provides a pinch of Kashmir to Pune people

items.name: Chitale Bandhu Mithaiwala
items.brandLongDescription: Started in 1950s, a foundation strongly engraved synonymous with quality, excellence and superior customer service, which has enabled the company to expand to international markets

items.name: City Bakery
items.brandLongDescription: City Bakery is one of the best bakeries in Pune, it is very famous for it's fruit cake.

items.name: Cream Craver
items.description: A popular fast food joint in Pune
items.brandLongDescription: It is a very popular eatery in the category of Fast Food segment in Pune. The belief that customer satisfaction is as important as their products and services, have helped this establishment garner a vast base of customers, which continues to grow by the day.

items.name: Degchi Biryani Cafe
items.brandLongDescription: Established in 1979 Degchi Biryani Cafe is popular for it's biryanis. They also serve other dishes but their biryani is simple heavenly specially for it's Bohri Biryani

items.name: Dohiti Bakerhouse
items.brandLongDescription: Dohiti Bakerhouse

items.name: Dorabjee And sons
items.brandLongDescription: Dorabjee and Sons are one of the oldest Parsi restaurants in India. The famous cuisines which every Punekar loves here are the famous Dhansak, Dum Biryani, Keema and Bheja.

items.name: Durva Modak Centre  -  Pune
items.brandLongDescription: Durva Modak Centre  -  PuneDurva Modak Centre  -  Pune

items.name: Fish Curry Rice
items.description: Restaurant specialising in Konkani fish preparations
items.brandLongDescription: Fish Curry Rice is a seafood restaurant located in Pune, it serves authentic Konkani specialities

items.name: Garden Vada pav
items.brandLongDescription: If you ever think that the vada pav culture is a tad bit overrated in Maharashtra, you are yet to visit the legendary Garden Vada Pav stall at Buttee Street in Camp. Always bustling with people, this food joint sells close to about 2,000 vada pavs a day and has been an unbeatable local fave since 1972.

items.name: Hotel Sandeep
items.brandLongDescription: This restaurant is famous for it's Maharashtrian cuisine. The receipes are awesome as well as pocket friendly. Shevga Handi, Chicken Kali Mirch, Mutton Biriyani, Mutton Ukad are the signature dishes of Hotel Sandeep.

items.name: IL Palazoo
items.brandLongDescription: IL Palazzo Hotel is Panchgani's oldest heritage resort. It is also very popular for it's Parsi food.

items.name: Joshi Wadewale
items.brandLongDescription: What started as an escape from ‘naukri’ is now one of the most famous Maharashtrian fast food chains in the city, also called the ‘McDonald’s of Pune’, Joshi Wadewale. Started in a 175 sq ft area, the first Joshi Wadewale outlet opposite Balgandharva, today spans across 2000 sq ft. The brand is now 17 outlets strong. And the last 22 years have seen it evolve and change, except one thing — Vasundhara’s wada pav recipe.

items.name: Karachi Sweet Mart
items.brandLongDescription: Parvati Foods (Karachi Sweet Mart)

items.name: Karachi sweets
items.brandLongDescription: Karachi Sweet Mart is a household name in Pune for lip-smacking sweets and savories. It has been serving the palates of sweet lovers with the widest variety of sweets which are prepared with the purest ingredients.

items.name: Kaveri
items.brandLongDescription: Established in the year 1996, Kaveri Restaurant in Wagholi, Pune is a top player in the category Maharashtrian Restaurants in the Pune. This well-known establishment acts as a one-stop destination servicing customers both local and from other parts of Pune.

items.name: Khichdi etc
items.brandLongDescription: Khichdi etc. serves authentic and fusion khichdis. Khichdi witnessed a new milestone on 4 Nov, 2017 in World India Food event, where over 800 kg of traditional Indian Khichdi made with rice, pulses, cereals and spices was promoted as Brand India Food, rightly capturing the distinctive feature of unity in diversity of Indian culture.

items.name: Kwality
items.brandLongDescription: A casual dining restaurant located in Pune. This Restaurant strive to provide you delicious food with excellent quality.  It offers a menu of different cuisine

items.name: Maganlal Chikki Products Pvt Ltd
items.brandLongDescription: Maganlal Chikki Pvt. Ltd is a snack company that was established in the year 1880. It has emerged as a fore-runner among other manufacturers, exporters and suppliers of yummy and nutritious Chikki, Fudges, Namkeens(Salties) and Sweets. Their fresh and pure products are completely lip-smacking and their tempting aroma makes it hard to resist them.

items.name: Malaka Spice
items.brandLongDescription: With several outlets across Pune, Malaka Spice has managed to emerge as one of the most sought-after restaurants for authentic Pan-Asian food since its inception in 1997. After all, this two-decade-old chain absolutely nails Malaysian, Thai, Japanese, Korean, and Vietnamese cuisines, with its traditional concoctions of each of these varieties.

items.name: Marz-O-Rin
items.brandLongDescription: With over 150 dishes Marz-O-Rin has over 150 dishes and is one of the most well-known bakeries in Pune. Their main dishes are sandwiches, rolls, and burgers, along with fruit drinks, milkshakes, and ice-creams.

items.name: Murphies
items.description: Murphies serves a fusion of Indian and International cuisine
items.brandLongDescription: Murphies seves a combination of comfort foods, appetizers and steaks. Trending ingredients, local produce and popular bar food from around the world is the basis for their menu.

items.name: Om Jai Shankar Pani Puri and Coldrinks House
items.brandLongDescription: There are very few places in pune where you get amazing Pani Puri and this is one of them. They have been serving from quite a long time and in the evening it's completely full. Their specialty is pani puri but you also get all kinds of Chaat.

items.name: Poona Cold Drink House
items.brandLongDescription: A perfect place for a sweet treat is Poona Cold Drink House at Camp, Pune. The brand was founded in the year 1973 with a small ice-cream joint. The response it received led to its successful journey, culminating in the establishment of a chain of ice-cream parlours all across the city.

items.name: Puneri Katta
items.brandLongDescription: Puneri Katta is very popular in Pune for authentic Maharashtrian food. It is a hot favouraite amongst the local Pune crowd

items.name: SP Biryani House
items.brandLongDescription: Started in 1994, SP Biryani has become the Biryani destination in Pune for its amazingly delicious aromatic traditional biryanis

items.name: Sahare Dining Hall
items.brandLongDescription: Established in the year 1992, Sahare Dining Hall, Pune is a top player in the category Gujarati Restaurants in the Pune. This well-known establishment acts as a one-stop destination servicing customers both local and from other parts of Pune. Over the course of its journey, this business has established a firm foothold in it’s industry. This famous restaurant serves cuisines like Gujarati, North Indian, Rajasthani, Indian.

items.name: Santosh Bakery
items.brandLongDescription: Santosh Bakery, Pune

items.name: Shahji By Kilo
items.brandLongDescription: Shahjis Rajdhani Caterers & Services is an organization hand-crafted by Jaideep Manchanda since 1999. A gifted entrepreneur and dynamic pillar of Pune's culinary eco-space, Jaideep Manchanda has through his perseverant innovations produced Shahjis Rajdhani Caterers & Services as a success story

items.name: Shahji Paratha House
items.brandLongDescription: Shahjis Rajdhani Caterers & Services is an organization hand-crafted by Jaideep Manchanda since 1999. A gifted entrepreneur and dynamic pillar of Pune's culinary eco-space, Jaideep Manchanda has through his perseverant innovations produced Shahjis Rajdhani Caterers & Services as a success story

items.name: Shree Narayan Khaman Dhokla And Sweets
items.brandLongDescription: Shree Narayan Khaman Dhokala And Sweets are manufacturer of samosa, khaman dhokla and sandwich dhokla from Pune, Maharashtra. This shop is a very well known brand for it's unique quality, variety, novelty and taste in Pune.

items.name: Shreyas Restaurant
items.brandLongDescription: Established in the year 1971, Shreyas Restaurant in pune is famous for its authentic Maharashtrian thalis and pure veg thalis

items.name: Signature Fine Dining
items.brandLongDescription: Signature Fine Dining is a new and ultimate destination for Mangalorean style seafood. They use fresh products to produce meals that combine vibrant flavours with appetizing looks.

items.name: Supriya Restaurant
items.brandLongDescription: About more than 30 years of serving with same zest and consistent quality, Supriya is one of the best South Indian restaurant in Pune. Though they serve North Indian food too but their South Indian is super popular.

items.name: Surves Pure Non Veg
items.brandLongDescription: Surve’s specialises in providing their patrons with lip-smacking Maharashtrian home-style delicacies such as mutton curry, chicken handi, bombil chutney and their specialities such as mutton kharda, takkar rassa handi and various others.

items.name: Swarajya Wadewale
items.brandLongDescription: Swarajya Wadewale from Pune as the name suggests is popular for all kinds of vadas in Pune

items.name: Tiranga Veg Non Veg Restaurant
items.brandLongDescription: Tiranga veg & non veg restaurant has a legendery status in Pune. This place has fabulous thalis but is also very well known for it's chicken biryani and mutton biryani.

items.name: kayani Bakery
items.description: Nostalgic Bakery super popular for Shrewsburry Biscuits
items.brandLongDescription: Established in 1955, Kayani Bakery is famous for Golden, buttery, melt-in-your-mouth Shrewsbury biscuits. Named after a town in Shropshire, England, Shrewsbury biscuits are synonymous with Kayani. A couple of these beauties won’t do your waistline any favours, but every bite is worth the inches. Kayani sells around 220-240 kg of these biscuits per day
